name: Society of Women Engineers
bio: SWE UW is committed to making STEM accessible and enjoyable to students from all backgrounds across Washington state.

name: Informatics Undergraduate Association
bio: We are an RSO that acts as the student government for Informatics students. We communicate between the Informatics student body, faculty, and administration of the University of Washington Information School. We host fun, community building events as well as events for professional development.

name: Lynnwood Kiwanis
bio: Kiwanis is a global organization of volunteers dedicated to improving the world one child and one community at a time. The Lynnwood Kiwanis Club is dedicated to serving the local community through various service and fundraising projects. Our club has been in service to our community for more than 56 years. We are part of Kiwanis International, an organization serving children for over 100 years.

name: UXPA Seattle
bio: We are a group of dedicated UX professionals who come together to promote social events, career workshops, portfolio reviews, and educational outreach to the greater Seattle area.

name: Boys & Girls Clubs of Bellevue
bio: Project Learn (Elementary) - Offers a variety of programs designed to increase academic performance including reading and writing practices, homework help, and fun activities. Trained, passionate staff facilitate data-driven programming to boost academic performance and social development of Club members.

name: Young Professional Communities
bio: YPCommunities is a landing pad designed to help young professionals connect to resources they need through virtual and in-person experiences. In the spirit of bridging the gap between people, businesses and their respective communities, YPC, the largest young professional network in the US, facilitates relationships locally while connecting thousands globally.

name: Sylvan Learning of Kirkland
bio: At Sylvan Learning of Kirkland, were focused on building academic confidence, igniting intellectual curiosity and inspiring a love for learning  all of which make a big impact in school and in life.Getting individualized, personal support will help your child truly grasp concepts. Our caring teachers are experts at encouraging and motivating kids to learn, grow and flourish.

name: Bellevue Rotary
bio: Founded in 1961, the Bellevue Rotary Club is an organization of local community and business leaders who make a difference by serving the citizens of our city and the world. Our primary avenues of service are Community Service, International Service, Vocational Service, and Youth Service.

name: Mentor Washington
bio: MENTOR Washington promotes, supports, and expands quality mentoring that fosters positive youth development, academic success, and job and career readiness.
